rows.text: Actor Matt McGorry (Orange is the New Black, How to Get Away with Murder) drops in to chat with Will about learning to drive at 28-years-old, camping, flexing his ass on TV, paparazzi and his social media skills.
Actor Taylor Kitsch (True Detective, Lone Survivor) drops-in to chat with Will about photography, focus, success, laziness, social media, charity and emergency landings.
Actor Brian Baumgartner (The Office) drops-in to chat with Will about singing in the high school choir, his friend "Michael Jordan" and people who annoy him.
In Part 1 of 2 with Paul Wesley, Will speaks with the actor about his perceived arrogance, mental therapy, directing, and lack of a daily routine.
In Part 2, Paul tells Will about the times that he has seen ghosts, how he got kicked out of school, and how he transitioned into acting full-time.
Will speaks with Modern Family creator Steve Levitan about being a boss, Midwest values, balance, tequila and Yelpers and Twitter'ers suck.
Will speaks with chef and TV host Anne Burrell about becoming a chef, sleeping in late and why emotions are heightened while on a plane.

On the eve of the US release of Captain America: Civil War, Will speaks with actor Sebastian Stan about managing relationships surrounding a massive premiere, growing up in a conservative home and the type of Uber driver he would be.
In Part 2 of Will's interview with Sebastian Stan, they talk about "first" experiences, Uber drivers for Trump and how Sebastian changed the Happy Meal forever.

Nico speaks with Will about getting sober, his experience in high school and how he went from being a really really ridiculously good-looking model to bring a really really ridiculously good-looking actor.

On the eve of the U.S. release of his new blockbuster film X-Men: Apocalypse, Evan Peters (American Horror Story) speaks about rap remixes of Adele songs, why he is annoyed by lap-napkins at restaurants, how to lose weight fast and what he learned on the set of X-Men.
In Part 2, Nico talks sexuality, becoming friends with police officers and why he has the nickname "The Hurricane."

On the eve of the 9th Anniversary of The Sopranos' historic series finale, Will speaks with the shows' star Rob Iler about the dentist, how much money he makes from The Sopranos today and why he likes getting his haircut in the bathtub.
Rob talks about why he hates House of Cards, why he loves Howard Stern and why he is weird about bathroom attendants. He also does some amazing impressions.
Chris raps the Ten Podcast Commandments and gives Will other lessons in podcasting and/or life.
Jenna Ushkowitz of Fox's hit TV show Glee chats with Will about not having "the talk" with her parents, throwing mirrors at the wall to get her way and losing a castmate.
Chace Crawford drops in to do his best impression of Scott Stapp of the band Creed, getting arrested, what he misses about Gossip Girl and his new project coming out next week "Undrafted"

In the Season 1 finale, Joe Mazzello talks about his fear of coming out of the lactose-intolerant closet, why he doesn't answer Harrison Ford's calls anymore and why he owes everything to Macaulay Culkin. Joe makes his directorial debut with "Undrafted" which hits theaters and iTunes today.
